  {
    "id": "stamp/signature-too-short",
    "rfc": 4,
    "kind": "validateStampSyntax",
    "input": {"method":"ed25519","identity":"did:mf:echo","at":"2026-05-07T12:00:00Z","signature":"c2hvcnQ="},
    "expect": {"ok": false, "reason": "signature-too-short"},
    "why": "A 64-byte Ed25519 signature is always exactly 88 base64 chars. The schema (minLength:88) and validator (length < 88) reject shorter strings. Note the DUAL finding: there is NO upper bound (signing-canon/signature-no-upper-bound), so a multi-megabyte 'signature' passes wire validation and is rejected only after full decode inside verify — see §9 open decision on canonical encoding."
  },
  {
