  {
    "id": "stamp/legacy-principal-key-rejected",
    "rfc": 4,
    "kind": "validateStampSyntax",
    "input": {"method":"ed25519","principal":"did:mf:echo","at":"2026-05-07T12:00:00Z","signature":"tK+CZ4Xb9WJ5cxE1RbldV+FOrqxLx7FgZIMHTZCBVStA0705NQHUumg7Lq0m3vrZS4GNcns7L3EaxzgWYmSgBA=="},
    "expect": {"ok": false, "reason": "legacy-principal-key"},
    "why": "R2 breaking cut (myelin#182): the stamp DID key is `identity`; the deprecated `principal` key was dropped from the wire and is now an unknown additional property. A stamp carrying `principal` (and thus no `identity`) is rejected. Pins the completed rename so a consumer cannot re-introduce the old key."
  },
  {
    "id": "stamp/at-calendar-blind-accepted",
    "rfc": 4,
    "kind": "validateStampSyntax",
    "input": {"method":"ed25519","identity":"did:mf:echo","at":"2026-13-40T25:99:99Z","signature":"tK+CZ4Xb9WJ5cxE1RbldV+FOrqxLx7FgZIMHTZCBVStA0705NQHUumg7Lq0m3vrZS4GNcns7L3EaxzgWYmSgBA=="},
    "expect": {"ok": true},
    "why": "FINDING, NOT A DESIGN (signing-canon/at-timestamp-three-strictness-levels). The deployed ISO-8601 regex is calendar-blind — month 13, day 40, hour 25 all pass wire validation. A conformant implementation of the DEPLOYED grammar MUST accept this string at the syntax layer. verify.ts then rejects it because Date.parse is non-finite, so the same value is wire-valid and verify-unparseable. The fix (a single calendar-valid rule) is called out in §9; this vector documents the current three-level behaviour honestly."
  }
